Comment in
    Blood. 1995 Dec 1;86(11):4382.

Within the Cooperative Study of Sickle Cell Disease, 694 infants with confirmed 
sickle cell disease were enrolled at less than 6 months of age. Information 
about the nature and frequency of complications was collected prospectively over 
a 10-year period. Painful crises and acute chest syndrome were the most common 
sickle cell-related events in homozygous sickle cell anemia (SS), hemoglobin SC 
